quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,O you enwrapped (in your raiment)
  73,2,"Rise up (to pray during) the night, except a little"
  73,3,"A half of it, or diminish a little thereof"
  73,4,Or increase thereto; and recite the Qur'an (in a distinct) recitation
  73,5,Surely We will soon cast upon you a weighty Saying
  73,6,Surely (prayer) by night is more intense in performance and more upright in (devotional) oration
  73,7,Surely in the daytime you have long employment
  73,8,"And remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself to Him with complete devotion"
  73,9,The Lord of the east and the west; there is no god except He; so take Him to yourself for an Ever-Trusted Trustee
  73,10,"And (endure) patiently what they (The disbelievers) say, and forsake them with a becoming forsaking"
  73,11,"And leave Me away (to deal) with the beliers, the ones endowed with (earthly) comfort, and give them more leisure for a little (while)"
  73,12,"Surely, close to Us are manacles and a (raging) Hell"
  73,13,"And food that chokes, (Literally: comprising choking) and a painful torment"
  73,14,"On the Day when the earth and the mountains will be in commotion, and the mountains become a heap of sand let loose"
  73,15,"Surely We have sent to you a Messenger as a witness over you, as We sent to Firaawn (Pharaoh) a Messenger"
  73,16,"Yet Firaawn disobeyed the Messenger, so We took him (away) a baneful (The root of the Arabic word implies death by droning) taking"
  73,17,"So, in case you disbelieve, how will you protect yourselves against a Day that will make the- newborn hoary-headed"
  73,18,Whereby the heaven will be rent asunder; His promise has (always) been performed
  73,19,Surely this is a Reminder; so let him who decides take for (himself) to his Lord a way